{"messages":[{"role":"user","content":"console.log nima?"},{"role":"assistant","content":"`console.log()` — bu JavaScriptda biror narsani konsolga (brauzer DevTools yoki terminal) chiqaradigan funksiya. Asosan debugging uchun ishlatiladi.\n\n```javascript\nconsole.log('Salom');  // chiqaradi: Salom\n```"}]}
{"messages":[{"role":"user","content":"What is console.log?"},{"role":"assistant","content":"`console.log()` is a JavaScript function that prints something to the console (browser DevTools or terminal). It's mostly used for debugging.\n\n```javascript\nconsole.log('Hello');  // prints: Hello\n```"}]}
{"messages":[{"role":"user","content":"useState nima?"},{"role":"assistant","content":"`useState` — bu React hook. Komponent ichida o'zgaruvchi (state) yaratish va uni o'zgartirish uchun ishlatiladi.\n\n```javascript\nconst [count, setCount] = useState(0);\nsetCount(count + 1); // count ni 1 ga oshiradi\n```"}]}
{"messages":[{"role":"user","content":"What is useState?"},{"role":"assistant","content":"`useState` is a React hook that lets you add state to a function component.\n\n```javascript\nconst [count, setCount] = useState(0);\nsetCount(count + 1); // increments count\n```"}]}
